\subtree{
\title{Assurance Levels (lowest to highest)}
\pre{\startverb
| Level | Meaning | Evidence Required |
|-------|---------|-------------------|
| Mentioned | Just referenced somewhere | Any doc |
\stopverb}

\p{<<<<<<< HEAD}

\pre{\startverb
| Designed | Has design doc | Design markdown |
| Specified | Has formal spec | Spec file |
| Implemented | Code exists | Source file + symbol |
| Tested | Has passing tests | Test file + test name |
| Proven | Has formal proof | Proof file + theorem |
\stopverb}

\p{=======}

\pre{\startverb
| Designed | Has design doc | docs/design/*.md |
| Specified | Has sigil spec | *.sigil file |
| Implemented | Code exists | Rust file + symbol |
| Tested | Has passing tests | Test file + test name |
| Proven | Has Lean proof | Lean file + theorem |
\stopverb}

\blockquote{>>>>>> origin/main}
}

\subtree{
\title{Claim Categories}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Feature}: User-visible functionality}
\li{\strong{Property}: System guarantee (linearizability, durability)}
\li{\strong{Guarantee}: Promise to users}
\li{\strong{Optimization}: Performance improvement}
\li{\strong{Invariant}: Internal system invariant}
\li{\strong{Decision}: Architectural choice with rationale}
\li{\strong{Omission}: Deliberate non-feature}
}

\p{<<<<<<< HEAD}
}

\subtree{
\title{Covariant Claim Structure}
\p{Claims form a presheaf over the assurance poset: higher assurance levels pull back evidence from lower levels. A Tested claim covariantly transports its Designed evidence forward.}

\pre{\startverb
Mentioned -> Designed -> Specified -> Implemented -> Tested -> Proven
\stopverb}

\p{Each arrow preserves evidence (covariant functor from assurance levels to evidence sets). =======}
}

\subtree{
\title{Evidence Types}
\pre{\startverb
// Documentation
Evidence::doc("docs/CLAIMS.md")

// Rust implementation
Evidence::rust("crates/foo/src/bar.rs", "SymbolName")

// Test file
Evidence::test("crates/foo/src/bar.rs", "test_prefix")

// Sigil specification
Evidence::sigil("sigil/specs/foo.sigil")

// External (benchmark, paper)
Evidence::external("benchmarks/harnesses/redis/src/main.rs")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Adding Claims}
\pre{\startverb
registry.register(
    Claim::new("CLM_UNIQUE_ID", "Short description")
        .with_category(Category::Feature)
        .with_component(Component::Slate)
        .with_assurance(Assurance::Implemented)
        .with_evidence(Assurance::Designed, Evidence::doc("docs/design/foo.md"))
        .with_evidence(Assurance::Implemented, Evidence::rust("crates/slate/src/lib.rs", "FooStruct"))
);
\stopverb}

\blockquote{>>>>>> origin/main}
}

\subtree{
\title{Extraction Process}
\subtree{
\title{1. Find Candidate Claims}
\p{<<<<<<< HEAD Scan sources for claim candidates:}

\pre{\startverb
grep -r "CLAIM\|GUARANTEE\|INVARIANT" docs/
grep -r "#\[test\]" -A 2 src/ | grep "fn test_"
grep -r "ops/s\|latency\|throughput" docs/
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Categorize by Irreducibility}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Irreducible claims}: Cannot be verified by simpler means (need full test execution)}
\li{\strong{Reducible claims}: Can be statically verified (type checking, linting)}
\li{\strong{Compositional claims}: Verified by composing sub-claim verifications}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Verify Evidence Paths}
\p{Before adding at Tested/Implemented level, verify paths exist.}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Downgrade Strategy}
\p{If evidence path is uncertain, downgrade assurance level. Upgrade later when evidence is confirmed.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Anti-Patterns}
\ul{
\li{Don't add Tested claims without verifying paths}
\li{Don't skip Designed level -- even Tested claims should have design evidence}
\li{Don't guess component names}
}

\p{======= Scan these sources for claim candidates:}

\pre{\startverb
# Explicit claims in docs
grep -r "CLM-\|CLAIM\|GUARANTEE\|INVARIANT" docs/

# Test names suggest guarantees
grep -r "#\[test\]" -A 2 crates/ | grep "fn test_"

# Performance claims
grep -r "ops/s\|latency\|throughput" docs/

# Sigil specs
find sigil/ -name "*.sigil" -exec grep -l "claim\|invariant\|property" {} \;
\stopverb}

\subtree{
\title{2. Categorize and Deduplicate}
\p{Group into tiers:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Tier 1 (SPEC_*)}: Claims with sigil specs - highest value}
\li{\strong{Tier 2 (TEST_*)}: Claims with test evidence}
\li{\strong{Tier 3}: Design-level claims (docs only)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Verify Evidence Paths}
\p{Before adding at Tested/Implemented level, verify paths exist:}

\pre{\startverb
# Check file exists
test -f "crates/basin-redis/src/crdt.rs" && echo "OK"

# Check symbol exists
grep -l "EntityStore" crates/basin-meta/src/indexes/*.rs
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Add to Registry}
\p{Add claims to \code{\startverb claims.rs\stopverb} in appropriate section:}

\ul{
\li{SPEC_* claims near line 1720}
\li{TEST_* claims after specs}
\li{PERF_* claims in performance section}
\li{Product claims (CLM_STASH, etc.) with products}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{CI Verification}
\p{The CI test filters claims at Tested/Proven level and verifies:}

\ol{
\li{Evidence file exists}
\li{Symbol/test found in file}
}

\pre{\startverb
# Run verification
graft test -p basin-norvid test_all_claims_verified
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Path Mappings}
\pre{\startverb
| Old/Wrong Path | Correct Path |
|----------------|--------------|
| `crates/stash/` | `crates/basin-redis/` |
| `crates/shelf/` | `crates/basin-mesh/` or `crates/spool-core/` |
| `crates/basin-jepsen/` | `tests/basin-jepsen/` |
| `products/nfs/tests/` | `crates/nfs/tests/` |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Downgrade Strategy}
\p{If evidence path is uncertain, downgrade to Designed level:}

\pre{\startverb
// Was Tested but can't verify path
.with_assurance(Assurance::Designed)
.with_evidence(Assurance::Designed, Evidence::doc("docs/CLAIMS.md"))
\stopverb}

\p{Upgrade later when evidence is confirmed.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Parallel Audit Pattern}
\p{For bulk verification, spawn sonnet agents:}

\pre{\startverb
Task: Audit PERF_* claims
- Check benchmark files exist
- Verify they actually measure what claim says
- Report which claims have valid evidence

Task: Audit product claims (CLM_STASH, etc.)
- Find actual test locations
- Verify symbol names
- Report path corrections needed
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Anti-Patterns}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Don't add Tested claims without verifying paths} - CI will fail}
\li{\strong{Don't embed large values in claim IDs} - Keep IDs short like \code{\startverb CLM_STASH\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Don't skip Designed level} - Even Tested claims should have design evidence}
\li{\strong{Don't guess component names} - Check \code{\startverb Component\stopverb} enum in identity.rs}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Reference}
\pre{\startverb
# Find existing claims
grep -n "Claim::new" crates/basin-norvid/src/claims.rs | head -20

# Check CI status
graft test -p basin-norvid test_all_claims_verified 2>&1 | grep -E "FAILED|passed"

# Find test files for a crate
find crates/basin-meta -name "*.rs" -exec grep -l "#\[test\]" {} \;

# Count claims by category
grep -E "Category::" crates/basin-norvid/src/claims.rs | sort | uniq -c
\stopverb}

\blockquote{>>>>>> origin/main}
}
}